### Solubility

Alkanes are soluble in non-polar solvents such as benzene. Big idea: polar solute tends to dissolve in polar solvents while non-polar solute tends to dissolve in non-polar solvent. The instantaneous dipole-induced dipole interaction between alkane molecules and the non-polar solvent molecules releases sufficient energy to overcome the instantaneous dipole-induced dipole attractions between the alkane molecules as well as that between the solvent molecules. Alkanes are insoluble in water and other highly- polar solvents such as ethanol. The instantaneous dipole-induced dipole interaction between alkane molecules and the water molecules does not release sufficient energy to overcome the stronger hydrogen bonds between the water molecules and the instantaneous dipole-induced dipole attractions between the alkane_

