### Combustion (SDL)

Alkanes react with excess oxygen to form carbon dioxide and water only. The complete combustion is a highly exothermic process.

General equation:

\[\mathrm{C_{n}H_{2n+2}\ +\ \frac{3n+1}{2}\,O_{2}\ \rightarrow\ nCO_{2}\ +\ (n+1)H_{2}O}\]

Example: Complete combustion of ethane gas

\[\mathrm{C_{2}H_{6}(g)\ +\ \frac{7}{2}\,O_{2}(g)\ \rightarrow\ 2CO_{2}(g)\ +\ 3H_{2}O(l)}\]

In a limited supply of oxygen, C, CO and H\({}_{2}\)O are formed.

Example: Incomplete combustion of methane gas

\[\mathrm{CH_{4}(g)\ +\ \frac{3}{2}\,O_{2}(g)\ \rightarrow\ CO(g)\ +\ 2H_{2}O(l)}\]

\[\mathrm{CH_{4}(g)\ +\ O_{2}(g)\ \rightarrow\ C(s)\ +\ 2H_{2}O(l)}\]

